    "It was at Kiel that he also met the early art historian of classical pottery, <a href=\"/jahno\">Otto Jahn</a>.": [],
    "Ross continued private study in Copenhagen where he secured the first travel scholarship offered by the King of Denmark.": [],
    "He also studied with Gottfried Hermann (1772-1848) in Leipzig.": [],
    "In 1832 he left for Greece where he was appointed ephor (magistrate) of antiquities of the Peloponnese the following year and general ephor in 1834.": [
